Very proud to be part of this crew and this incredible award-winning film! 

As an Associate Producer of this documentary- I am touched to finally see a film that sets the story straight about the true history of the Cannabis industry leading up to legalization and how #OU was the life force behind it all. We have won so many awards and are being asked to be part of film festivals all around the world simply because Cannabis is a GLOBAL human rights issue.

I started with @oaksterdamuniversity as a student over two decades ago and have been with #OU ever since. 

I now proudly serve as Chairwoman for Oaksterdam’s Nonprofit for Education “O.N.E” We provide scholarships to those who have been negatively impacted by the BS “War-On-Drugs”. 

We have given graciously to @lastprisonerproject @40tonsbrand & many other organizations working to right all the wrong in our beloved industry.

I’m calling on all loved ones and our friends in the industry that we have supported in the past to now support OU back through watching this film and spreading the word.

December 3 is our next film premiere in #NYC and we would love and hope to see you there.

If you are a company and want to get involved further- shoot me a DM because we need your support! TAG YOUR FAVORITE CANNABIS COMPANIES!!

Until then PUFF PUFF PASSSSS 😍💨💨💨 #DonKatzir #RavitMarkus @jeffj420 @daleskyjones @americanpotstory

NYC premiere on Sunday Dec 3rd 4:15 at @danceswithfilms. Tickets link in bio. Get them before we sell out. Special guests: @daleskyjones @priscillapyrk of @oaksterdam.nonprofit and director @ravitmarkus
